#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:41
msgid ""
"That is, patterns more complex than `_, foo, &foo, &&foo, mut foo` are "
"forbidden."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:44
msgid ""
"Inconsistency between default implementations in traits and implementations "
"in impl blocks"
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:59
msgid ""
"Inconsistency between method declarations in traits and in extern blocks"
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:66
msgid "\"C\""
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:71
msgid ""
"Slightly more complicated syntax analysis for LL style parsers. The parser "
"must guess if it currently parses a pattern or a type."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:74
msgid ""
"Small complications for source code analyzers (e.g. [IntelliJ Rust](https://"
"github.com/intellij-rust/intellij-rust/"
"commit/1bb65c47341a04aecef5fa6817e8b2b56bfc9abb#diff-66f3ba596f0ecf74a2942b3223789ab5R41)) "
"and potential alternative implementations."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:77
msgid ""
"Potential future parsing ambiguities with named and default parameters "
"syntax."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:81
msgid "None of these issues is significant, but they exist."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:84
msgid ""
"Even if we exclude these technical drawbacks, it can be argued that allowing "
"to omit parameter names unnecessary complicates the language. It is "
"unnecessary because it does not make Rust more expressive and does not "
"provide noticeable ergonomic improvements. It is trivial to add parameter "
"name, and only a small fraction of method declarations actually omits it."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:90
msgid ""
"Another drawback of this syntax is its impact on the learning curve. One "
"needs to have a C background to understand that `fn foo(T);` means a "
"function with single parameter of type `T`. If one comes from dynamically "
"typed language like Python or JavaScript, this `T` looks more like a "
"parameter name."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:95
msgid ""
"Anonymous parameters also cause inconsistencies between trait definitions "
"and implementations. One way to write an implementation is to copy the "
"method prototypes from the trait into the impl block. With anonymous "
"parameters this leads to syntax errors."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:105
msgid "Detailed design"
msgstr "詳細設計"

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:109
msgid "Backward compatibility"
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:111
msgid ""
"Removing anonymous parameters from the language is formally a breaking "
"change. The breakage can be trivially and automatically fixed by adding `_:` "
"(suggested by @nagisa):"
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:124
msgid ""
"However this is also a major breaking change from the practical point of "
"view. Parameter names are rarely omitted, but it happens. For example, `std::"
"fmt::Display` is currently defined as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:134
msgid ""
"Of the 5560 packages from crates.io, 416 include at least one usage of an "
"anonymous parameter ([full report](https://github.com/rust-lang/rfcs/"
"pull/1685#issuecomment-238954434))."
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:140
msgid "Benefits of deprecation"
msgstr ""

#: src/1685-deprecate-anonymous-parameters.md:142
msgid ""
"So the proposal is just to deprecate this syntax. Phasing the syntax out of "
"usage will mostly solve the learning curve problems. The technical problems "
"would not be solved until the actual removal becomes feasible and practical. "
"This hypothetical future may include:"
msgstr ""

